[TabItem] DAZN GLOBAL PRIVACY NOTICE
Last updated
: 21/06/2023
The
DAZN Global Privacy Notice
outlines how we collect and use your personal information when you access, visit or otherwise make use of our services – websites, applications, products, and/or content. It should be read and understood in in conjunction with our local Terms and Conditions, our Global Cookie Notice
and any applicable specific Privacy Notice provided by DAZN with regards to certain services offered by DAZN.
This Privacy Notice has been developed as a global notice in accordance with applicable data protection law in the countries where we operate. We provide additional information to account for varying legislative provisions in certain countries and will present these to you automatically depending on your global location.
1. WHO WE ARE
We are DAZN Limited (“we”, “us”, or “our”) – better known as DAZN – and we act as the data controller of your personal information. We are registered with the UK Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO):
Registration number: ZA253941
Registered office: DAZN Limited, 12 Hammersmith Grove, London, W6 7AP, United Kingdom
2. TYPES OF INFORMATION WE COLLECT
We collect and use various types of personal information about you to provide, promote and improve our services. For simplicity, we have grouped the information we collect into different categories set out below.
Account information
Information associated with creating and managing your user account, including your name, email address, address, account ID, identification (for age-verification purposes), age, date of birth, telephone number, activation code, subscription type and account preferences.
Payment information
Information associated with collecting payments from you for the provision of our services, including bank account number, payment/credit card or other payment method details, payments to/from you directly or indirectly, and your invoice and transaction details.
Usage information
Information about your use, activity and interaction with our content and services, including platform navigation, pages viewed, content watched, and search queries.
Technical information
Information
about your device or browser used to access our services and other technical information, including your
IP address
and device or unique identifiers. For
more information about our use of cookies and similar technologies please read our
Cookie Notice
.
Customer Service information
Information where you chose to interact with our customer services teams, including chat conversation transcripts, contact information and detail regarding the reasons for contacting us.
Feedback and Survey information
Information provided where you have chosen to participate in surveys, beta tests or any other feedback engagement, including reviews, suggests or ratings of content.
Marketing information
Information provided by you about your preferences to receive marketing communications from us and third parties, or where you participate in promotions, prize draws and competitions, and direct marketing communications with you, including emails, push-notifications, text messages.
Advertising information
Information about your preferences to receive tailored advertising on our platforms, and/or in combination with the Technical information (see above), used by us and third parties to select, display and measure the use of tailored and non-tailored advertising.
More information about advertising can be found in our
Cookie Notice
.
Aggregated information
We also collect, store, use and share aggregated information such as statistical or demographic information. This could be derived from your personal information but is not itself considered personal information. Should this data be combined with any personal identifier, the provisions of this Privacy Notice will apply, and the aggregate data would be treated as personal.
We do not collect any
special categories
of personal information about you: this includes details about your race or ethnicity, religious or philosophical beliefs, sex life, sexual orientation, political opinions, trade union membership, information about your health, and genetic or biometric information.
3. HOW WE COLLECT YOUR INFORMATION
Information you give us
For the most part we collect and use your personal information that is provided to us when you register for, subscribe to or otherwise use our services. Examples of information you may give us include the following categories outlined in Types of Information We Collect: Account information, Customer Service information, Marketing information, Feedback and Survey information and Advertising information.
Information we collect automatically
We may automatically collect and use personal information about your device and your use of, and interactions with, our services. We do this through a variety of technical methods, including the collection of personal information and information via cookies and similar technologies. For more information, please read our Cookie Notice.
Information we receive from other sources
We collect and use personal information about you from other sources and from third parties to the extent permitted by applicable law. We combine and connect the personal information we collect from and about you with personal information we receive from these other sources. Where personal information is transferred to us from third parties, we take steps to verify that these third parties are legally permitted to disclose this information to us.
Examples of information we might receive include personal information and information from other entities within DAZN, third party databases (such as publicly available databases) and other third-party services providers and partners such as:
Payment service providers and processors (e.g. providing us with payment information associated with your purchases of our services).
Service delivery providers
(e.g. a mobile carrier or set top box operator who makes available our Services on its device).
Service providers (e.g. location data to customise our Services and content available to you, online and offline demographic information, interest-based and online advertising related information).
Identity/account authorisation and identification services (e.g. where you choose to login to our services via a third-party account such as Google).
Voice assistant platform providers who enable interaction with our Services through voice commands (e.g. Amazon Alexa, Apple Siri).
4. PURPOSES AND USE OF YOUR INFORMATION
Legal Basis
We, or organisations acting on our behalf, may use your personal information for justified and specified purposes, and in each instance, relying on an applicable lawful basis under applicable data protection law. These bases include:
Consent
: where you have given permission for us to process your personal information for one or more specific purposes.
You have the right to withdraw your consent at anytime, but this will not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.
Performance of contract
: where processing your personal information is necessary for a contract to which you are a party.
Legal Obligation
: where processing your personal information is necessary for us meet our legal and regulatory compliance requirements in the countries where we operate.
Legitimate Interests
: where processing your personal information is necessary for our own or a third parties justified legitimate interests, and where your rights and freedoms do not override those interests.
We process your personal information for the following purposes under each lawful basis as set out below.
Consent
We may rely on your consent to occasionally send you specific direct marketing communications about offers and updates from our partners that we think may be of interest to you; you find the full list of our partners
here
. Where consent is relied upon you will have actively agreed to the processing and have been presented with specific information about the activity.
Outside of cases where email is used as a contact channel (for which legitimate interest is applicable, as set out below in the section on "Legitimate Interests"), we may rely on your consent to occasionally send you via other contact channels that you can select from the Preference Centre (push notification, SMS, WhatsApp) communications relating to DAZN offers, content and features similar to those you have already purchased from DAZN.
Where legally required, we will collect your consent store and/or access information on your device (e.g. Technical Information)
, the use of cookies or other mobile identifiers, and the collection, sharing and use of personal information for tailored advertisements (ads) on our services, as well as to combat fraud and abuse, to prevent you seeing the same adverts repeatedly and for aggregated ad reporting.
For more information, please read our Cookie Notice
.
Contract
To register you as a new user and create your account.
To provide you with our services, including creating and administering your account, identifying and authenticating you, sending statements and invoices to you, collecting and processing payments from you, and playing content.
To provide you with location-based services (e.g. to enforce territorial restrictions of content available based on your location).
To administer and monitor our services, including notify you about changes or updates to our services and any issues with our services, such as unavailability.
To provide technical and customer support, including dealing with enquiries and complaints.
To notify you about changes to our Terms and Conditions, this Privacy Notice and/or any other terms and conditions relevant to our services.
Legal Obligation
To enable us to comply with any legal or regulatory requirements and otherwise comply with the direction of any relevant regulatory or competent authority.
To prevent, detect, investigate and mitigate prohibited or illegal activities, including fraud and money laundering.
To ensure information security of your personal information.
To retain and store your personal information to comply with specific legal retention requirements, regulatory audits, and other record keeping purposes.
Legitimate Interests
For processing purposes based on our legitimate interests, we have provided the information from our balancing test when assessing whether each processing purpose constitutes ‘necessary’ processing for our own or a third party’s own purposes, to ensure processing does not override your
rights and freedoms.
Our processing purpose
Ours or a third party’s legitimate interest
To prevent, detect, mitigate and investigate suspected or actual fraud, security breaches and other unlawful or harmful activities.
Protect our business, our services and its users from fraudulent or otherwise unlawful or harmful activities.
To monitor and improve the information security of our services.
Keep our services (including our related intellectual property rights) and your personal information secure and to mitigate the risk of accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, unauthorised disclosure of, or access to, your personal information.
To use data analytics, research, development, testing and analysis to improve and enhance our services, to diagnose and fix problems and develop and test new content, products, services and features.
Keep our services updated and relevant, to optimise user experience, to inform our marketing, advertising and content strategy, and otherwise to develop and grow our business.
To detect abuse of our services.
Protect our business and mitigate the risk of unauthorised use (including piracy).
To monitor compliance with and to enforce our Terms and Conditions (including, but not limited to, determining free trial eligibility or the use of a number of devices in violation of the Terms and Conditions), this Privacy Notice and other rules and policies.
Protect our business and mitigate the risk of unauthorised use.
To compile and use Aggregated Information for internal and external business purposes.
To use Aggregated Information to better understand our users and how they use our services, to report on the effectiveness of content to rights holders and advertising campaigns to ad partners, to inform our marketing, advertising and content strategy, and otherwise to develop and grow our business.
For profiling purposes so that we can (subject to any preferences you have expressed (including consent, where required)) build a profile about you and your interests to:
understand and respect your preferences
understand and analyse customer trends and patterns, so that we can enhance and improve our services
offer you on-product personalisation of content, including by suggesting and delivering recommended content (e.g. via in-app notifications and/or push notifications) and providing personalised search and content;
show you tailored ads that are relevant to you; and
send more effective direct marketing communications related to our services.
Better understand our users and how they use our services, to provide a more personalised and tailored user, content, advertising and marketing communication experience to you, and to develop and grow our business.
You are free to opt-out of personalisation of content – see the Direct Marketing
section.
More information on opting-out of tailored ads can be found in our
Cookie Notice.
To technically deliver ads and/or content on our services.
For ours and our advertising partners’ legitimate interests to allow you to see and interact with ads on our services.
To select and display basic and non-tailored ads, measure ad performance, and generate audience insights from ads displayed to you on our Services (subject to any preferences you have expressed (including consent, where required)).
For ours and our advertising partners’ legitimate interests to:
display ads to you based on the content you are viewing, the app you are using, your general location, or your device type (including to control the frequency and sequence of ads shown to you); and
measure the performance and effectiveness of ads that you see or interact with.
To make ads displayed to you on our services more relevant and tailored to you and your interests (subject to any preferences you have expressed (including consent, where required)).
Use the information we and our advertising partners hold about you to help us sell our ad inventory and to make the ads you see more relevant and tailored to your interests.
You are free to opt-out of tailored ads on our services at any time. More information on opting-out of tailored ads can be found in our Cookie Notice.
To market our services - subject to any preferences you have expressed, including consent, where required - including:
send exclusively by email communications relating to offers, contents and functionalities of DAZN similar to those already purchased by you from DAZN;
delivering direct marketing communications to you across various channels/platforms, such as email, text message, online, device notifications (both push and in-app) or otherwise to inform you about news, products, services, promotions and special offers which we think might be of interest to you;
showing you targeted and relevant marketing communications and ads about our services on a selection of websites across the Internet and social media platforms using both cookies (see our
Cookie Notice
) and ‘protected identifier matching’ (see
Direct Marketing
section);
contacting you in respect of market research, surveys and beta testing programmes, so that we can improve the Services we offer; and
measuring and analysing the effectiveness and reach of such marketing communications and ads.
Show you more relevant marketing and advertising related to our services, to better target prospective customers who have shown an interest in our services (e.g. by navigating to our websites or applications), and to analyse the performance of our marketing communications and advertising.
To process your information to send you direct marketing communications relating to similar goods and services to the one you have taken out or have expressed an interest in.
You are free to opt-out of direct marketing communications at any time – see the
Direct Marketing
section.
To administer competitions and other offers/promotions which you enter, including sending you prizes won.
Enable us to process entries to select winners and issue prizes to these winners.
To geo-block content on our Services.
For ours and our rights holders to only show you content when you are in the relevant territories, except when legally permitted.
To provide our commercial partners with information about users’ use of any co-branded parts of our services, including historical use data.
For the purposes of meeting our contractual obligations.
5. HOW WE SHARE YOUR INFORMATION
We share your personal information and other information as set out below. Where we disclose your personal information to service providers or third parties, we require them to respect the security of your personal information, to treat it in accordance with applicable law, and to use it only for specified and authorised purposes.
Service providers
We disclose your information to third party service providers authorised by us and acting on our behalf to operate functions of our services. We have agreements in place with these third-party service providers to ensure that they keep your information secure: they only process it in accordance with our instructions and as necessary to perform authorised purposes necessary for the relevant part of our services to operate (and for no other purpose).
Our partners
Where legally permitted, we may share your personal information with partners such as mobile carriers, TV/games console manufacturers, and/or set top box operators to coordinate with them on providing our services to their customers.
DAZN Channels
If you have subscribed to receive certain channels within DAZN, we may share certain data with the relevant content provider named below, as follows:
