Professional advisers
We share your personal information to our professional advisers and the professional advisers of other DAZN entities including lawyers, bankers, auditors, insurers and accountants.
Business transfers and transactions
In the event of any reorganisation, restructuring, merger or sale, or other transfer of assets, we will transfer information, including your personal information, provided that the receiving party agrees to treat your personal information in a manner that is consistent with this Privacy Notice.
Fraud prevention
In order to detect, investigate and prevent fraud, money laundering and other harmful or unlawful activities, we may disclose your personal information and information to third parties including, but not limited to, any relevant regulator, financial institutions and law enforcement agencies or any other body that deals with the investigation of alleged offences or unlawful activities.
Other lawful reasons
We share your personal information and other information with third parties where we are under a duty to, or reasonably believe we need to, disclose or share your personal information in order to:
comply with any applicable law, regulation, legal obligation or regulatory/law enforcement authority request;
enforce or apply our Terms and Conditions (including any related investigations); and
protect against harm to the rights of DAZN, its rights holders and/or its users (including related to piracy or the threat of piracy), as permitted by applicable law.
6. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS
DAZN is a global organisation, and your personal information may be transferred, stored and processed between any of the countries in which we, our entities or third parties operate for any of the purposes set out above.
For such international transfers we ensure the appropriate safeguarding of your personal information through only transmitting information via transfer mechanisms approved by the applicable data protection laws:
the European Commission or UK government, as applicable based on the country whereby the DAZN services are offered, has determined that an adequate level of protection for your personal information is in place in the country to which we transfer your personal information (e.g. Canada and Japan);
standard data protection clauses as adopted by the European Commission or UK government are in place governing the transfer.
for transfers to the USA, the recipient is a participant in an agreed EU-US data transfer programme (or equivalent with the UK) as and when created; or
other appropriate safeguards in accordance with applicable law have been put in place.
Information in relation to mechanisms governing these transfers can be requested via the
Contact Us
section.
7. RETENTION OF YOUR INFORMATION
We will only retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfil the purpose for which it was collected, or to comply with legal, regulatory, or internal policy requirements. For the majority of information we hold, this will be seven years from the retention event. To determine the appropriate retention periods, we consider:
the amount, nature and sensitivity of your personal information.
the potential risk of harm from unauthorised use or disclosure of your personal information.
the purposes for which we process your personal information and whether we can achieve those purposes through other means.
the applicable legal, regulatory, tax, accounting or other requirements for retention
8. YOUR RIGHTS
Depending on applicable data protection laws, you are able to exercise your rights in respect of your personal information we process:
To request a copy of the personal information we hold about you.
To request correction or rectification of your personal information where it is inaccurate or incomplete.
To request the erasure of your personal information where processing is no longer necessary for the purposes for which it was collected.
To request the restriction of processing of your personal information.
To request transfer of your personal information to another data controller.
To object to your personal information being used for direct marketing or where the processing is based on our legitimate interests except where we can demonstrate compelling grounds for continuing.
To withdraw consent where we have asked for your consent to process your personal information; this includes withdrawal of consent from direct marketing communications.
To not to be subject to decisions made automatically that produce legal effects or significantly affect you. However, our use of profiling and automated decision-making is
not
considered to produce legal effects or significantly affect you.
To exercise your rights, please see the
Contact Us
section. We may not be able to comply with your request based on exceptions that we can rely upon under applicable data protection laws associated with your country of residence. Should this be the case, we would inform you of this when you contact us.
We will acknowledge requests immediately and without delay and will aim to complete your request within one calendar month;
such a period may be extended by two further months where necessary, taking into account the complexity and number of the requests. If needed, we will inform you of any such extension within one month of receipt of the request, together with the reasons for the delay.
Where required we will take reasonable and appropriate steps to verify your identify when making a request, or the authorisation of third parties making a request on your behalf, to comply with applicable data protection laws and ensure the security of your personal information.
9. DIRECT MARKETING
Subject to your preferences (including consent, where required), we collect and use your personal information to send you direct marketing communications about our services, or services of our Partners, via email, push notification, protected identifier matching, and text message. You can amend any of the above preferences via the marketing Preference Centre in your DAZN account or, in the case of emails, by clicking on the 'Unsubscribe' link in the footer of the email.
10. CHILDREN'S INFORMATION
Unless otherwise stated in localised privacy notices in accordance with applicable data protection law in the countries where we operate, you must be 18 years of age or older to subscribe to our services. We do not knowingly collect and/or share personal information about children and take steps to delete such information without notification should we become aware of such processing. If you are a parent or guardian and have reason to believe that we have collected personal information from or about your child, please contact us via the methods in the
Contact Us
section.
11. INFORMATION SECURITY
We are committed to protecting your personal information, and to do so we deploy industry-standard physical, technical and organisational security measures in the collection, storage, use and transfer of your information. Whilst no security measures are impenetrable, the controls we apply are designed to maintain the confidentiality, integrity and availability of your personal information.
You also have a part to play to safeguard your personal information and you help can do this by:
Keeping your username and password for your DAZN account secure.
Using a different password on your DAZN account to those used on your other personal accounts.
Updating your devices with the most recent software patches, and by installing an anti-virus product to help protect against malware.
Should you suspect malicious use of or access to your DAZN account or have received a suspicious email claiming to be from DAZN, please contact us via the methods in the
Contact Us
section.
12. CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY NOTICE
We keep this notice under regular review to ensure it reflects how we process your personal information, including changes to our processing purposes, your rights in respect of your personal information, and substantive or material changes to how we process personal information. We may take proactive measures to notify you of any such changes via an appropriate means to ensure you remain informed, such as emails, and website pop ups.
13. CONTACT US
If you have any questions in respect of this Privacy Notice, about the collection and processing of your personal information, or to exercise your rights, please contact
datasubjectrights@dazn.com
.
14. COMPLAINTS
In the first instance, you can raise an issue regarding your personal information to DAZN’s Data Protection Officer (DPO) via
DPO@dazn.com
.
If you have contacted us regarding your personal information and are still not satisfied with our response and in any other case, you have the right to lodge a complaint with your local supervisory authority.
